{{{
Predicates:
British(x) ::: x is a British Sitcom series.
Pappy(x) ::: x is a member of Pappy's.
ScriptEditor(x, y) ::: x was the script editor for y.
WorkingTitle(y, z) ::: y has the working title z.
Premises:
British(badults) ∧ ∃x (Pappy(x) ∧ Star(x, badults)) ::: Badults is a British Sitcom series, starring members of Pappy's.
Piloted(badults, july2013) ::: Badults piloted in July 2013 on BBC Three.
WorkingTitle(badults, theSecretDudeSociety) ::: The Working title "The Secret Dude Society" was used for Badults.
ScriptEditor(andrewCollins, badults) ::: Andrew Collins was the script editor for Badults
Conclusion:
∃x (British(x) ∧ ScriptEditor(andrewCollins, x) ∧ WorkingTitle(x, theSecretDudeSociety)) ::: Andrew Collins was the script editor for a series with the working title "The Secret Dude Society".
}}}
}}}

{{{
Predicates:
Happy(x) ::: x is a happy event.
Sad(x) ::: x is a sad event.
Premises:
∀x (Event(x) → Happy(x) ⊕ Sad(x)) ::: Events are either happy or sad.
∃x (Event(x) ∧ Happy(x)) ::: At least one event is happy.
Conclusion:
¬∀x (Event(x) → Sad(x)) ::: All events are sad.
}}}
